This traditional style of cooking over the fire, popularly known as a braai in South Africa, has never come so handy in recent times and this Sunday making lamb shanks over a potije sounds about right.  This recipe is courtesy of the man who created Braai Day, Jan Braai, real name Jan Scannell in 2007, also releasing a cookbook of the same name.   These lamb shanks will fall off the bone as they need to be gently cooked for a period of time.  Feeds 6 ALSO TRY: Recipe of the day: One pot lamb shanks with button mushrooms This recipe can be found on melkbos.net.